  <data name="rtbHowToPlay.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>
The goal of each player is to get rid of their total cards the fastest. The order of the cards is next,
from the weakest to the strongest: 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, Jack, Queen, King, Ace. No matter what, the 
trump card is the strongest out of all the other cards.

In the beginning of the turn, it is advisable to designate a Durak in order to know who plays 
first and who distributes.

the Durak distributes 6 cards to each player, the extra card form the draw pile. The first card of
the draw pile is returned and is placed under it, its color indicates the trump suit, it will be the 
last card drawn. If we play 6, there is no draw, the asset being designated be the color of the 
last card of the Durak (which must then show to the other players)

This is how the game is played:

The first attacker is the player situated to the right of the Durak, the Durak being the first 
defender. If the attack is successful, the defender becomes the attacker challenging in turn the
player on the left. If the attack fails, the defender passes their turn and its the player on the left
who becomes the attacker, he challeneges the player placed directly to the left.

To win the defender, so at the start the Durak must give a stronger card than that posed or an 
asset. The attacker and the other players (unless the game is played by a team) may lay cards 
of the same value as the cards already laid.

When the defender has no cards, they can't play anymore or when the attackers can no longer
put cards, the turn ends.

The first attacker takes the cards in the draw pile until they get 6 cards, then each of the attackers 
does the same in a clockwise direction and finally the defender does the same. The Durak is 
the player that has cards left at the end of the game. If the Durak loses on an attack four 6 
attack then it is said to have taken its gallons.

